THE Vesta Orchestra has announced its January 2022 edition of the Afri-Classical Concert Series. The event, it was gathered, will hold on Sunday, January 30, 2022, by 5 pm, at the Terra Kulture Arena, Victoria Island, Lagos.   Portable laments excessive demands by sex workers     Go buy credit, Vee teases Laycon over Snapchat call     REMINISCE: Members of my family say I’m Makanaki without…   The Afri-Classical concert series is dedicated to showcasing music by highlife and classical composers from Africa. The January 2022 edition promises to be an exciting evening filled with Nigerian highlife, opera excerpts, ballet, and art music. Founded by Rosalyn Aninyei, the orchestra will be conducted by Fope Onalaja. The Vesta Orchestra can be reached on their various Social media platforms.